1.title: Best Weekend Car
1.plot: T-Pain, Oliver Trevena, Mischa Barton, and Brian Vickers hold the keys to some of the coolest cars on the planet. They'll push them to their limits to find the perfect ride for any vibe. Weekend drives are all about fun, so what would you choose: a Porsche GT3 RS, Mercedes Benz SLS AMG Roadster, 1976 Ford Bronco or a 1966 Corvette Stingray?

2.title: Best of British
2.plot: British cars are known as some of the most fun and luxurious cars in the world. We'll take some of their best out to Willow Springs International Raceway, including a Rolls Royce Wraith, a Jaguar F-Type R, an Aston Martin Vantage and everyone's little favorite: the Mini John Cooper Works Convertible.

3.title: High Performance Cars
3.plot: Many of today's high performance cars seem more ready for the race track then city streets, but our four car lovers will test them in both places. They'll drive the Ferrari 458 Italia Spider, the Lamborghini Aventador, The McLaren 650S and the Audi R8 Spyder.

4.title: Iconic Trucks
4.plot: From luxurious style to off-road adventure to cruising the street, these truck haul more than just a payload, and our four hosts hold the keys to some remarkable machines. The 1994 Land Rover Defender 90, the 1953 ICON Thriftmaster, 1971 El Camino SS, and the 2016 Ram Rebel will be road tested near the shipping docks in Los Angeles.

5.title: Cars of the 1980's
5.plot: The 1980's unleashed a revolution in automotive design and performance. Now, these 80's babies are all grown-up and ready to test-drive: the Buick Grand National GNX, the BMW M3, Alfa Romero Spider Veloce and the pop culture icon, the DeLorean DMC-12.

6.title: Muscle Cars
6.plot: Muscle Cars featured in the Season 1 Finale are: '70 Dodge Super Bee, '68 Chevy Camaro SS, '69 Dodge Charger, '68 Pontiac GTO.

imdb.plot outline: Rapper T-Pain, professional race car driver Brian Vickers, actress Mischa Barton, and actor Oliver Trevena hit the road in some of the most incredible new and vintage cars out there, pushing them to the limit in a battle to determine the absolute all-time best cars in a variety of categories. Premieres November 15 only on Esquire Network.
